cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SD, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the problem of finding a group of people based on social, spatial, and keyword constraints. This problem is related to social networks and information retrieval, which are covered by cs.SI and cs.IR respectively. The paper also proposes a search framework that involves efficient search algorithms and data structures, which are related to database systems (cs.DB) and spatial data analysis (cs.SD). Finally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to extract keywords from user profiles, which is related to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
